title: For Sale/Trade:  FEG PA-63 pistol (Hungary) - Military
postcontent:
Characteristics

Type	 Double Action semiautomatic
9x18 Mak in PA-63
Weight unloaded	 595 g
Length	 175 mm
Barrel length	 100 mm
Magazine capacity	 7 rounds
The FEG PA-63 pistol was developed during early 1960s at the Hungarian FEG arms factory as a compact military sidearm, chambered for the Warsaw pact standard 9x18 Makarov ammunition of Soviet origin. The basic design of the FEG PA-63 pistol was heavily based on the German Walther PP pistol, a copy of which was produced by FEG shortly after the WW2. FEG also produced a number of derivatives of the PA-63, such as 'export commercial' model AP-63, chambered for widely available 9x17 Browning / .380 ACP and 7.65 Browning / .32ACP ammunition. Both PA-63 and AP-63 pistols were similar in design, and differed only in ammunition used and in frame finish - military-issue PA-63 pistols had their aluminum frames left 'in the white', while commercial AP-63 pistols have their aluminum frames finished in same black color as the rest of the gun.
The FEG PA-63 pistol is a simple blowback operated weapon. The return spring is located around the barrel, the trigger is of traditional double-action type with exposed hammer. Manual safety lever, which doubles as a decocker, is located at the left side of the slide. Gun is fed from single stack box magazines, magazine release button is located on the left side of the frame, above and behind the trigger.

The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC‚Äôs first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1‚Äù overall length and an 18.5‚Äù cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3‚Äù rounds in total (6 per tube). TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

Caliber	12 gauge 3‚Äù

Total capacity

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale:  Flow chart for anyone who uses this site
postcontent:
Here's a little flow chart to help you all post:

                               Are you selling a firearm?
                             /                                     \
                          Yes                                    No
                           /                                          \
                  Post in "firearms"                        Don't post in "firearms" 
                                     \ 
                                Can you buy the gun cheaper online?
                                 /                                     \
                             Yes                                      No
                           /                                              \
                  Lower your price                                  \
                                           \                                 /
                                              \                             /
                                                 Is your gun "rare"?
                                               /                            \
                                            Yes                             No
                                              \                              /
                                               Liar                       /     
                                                   \                     /
                                                Is your gun used? 
                                              /                          \
                                          Yes                          No
                                          /                                \
                           What condition is it?                  GO POST!
                          /                            \
                       Great!                       Acceptable
                          \                                  \
         What condition is it actually in?        GO POST!
                             \
                        Acceptable
                                 \
                           GO POST!


Hopefully you find this helpful and please, please, please use it for every post.

Made by Beretta, this is a high-quality .25 caliber semi-auto pistol with an innovative and unique ‚Äútip-up‚Äù barrel that makes cleaning the bore, and topping off the gun a breeze! No need to rack the slide to chamber a round, just push a lever and barrel tips up: load a round, snap it shut, cock the hammer and fire away! 8 rounds in the magazine plus one in the chamber. The pistol is finished in a matte black with black plastic factory grips with the Beretta logo. The pistol is in very good condition, it has some use marks and light scratches on the finish, and extremely minor wear to the grips, overall condition is 90+%. The bore is crisp with good rifling, and trigger pull is smooth. 

While .25 ACP is a somewhat anemic caliber, I don‚Äôt think anybody will volunteer to get shot with it, and this little Beretta is better than carrying nothing, especially in hot weather clothing, and a .25 is definitely a good back-up to your regular concealed carry handgun. Due to it being a center fire round, it is inherently more reliable than any .22 rim fire. I have fired at least 500 rounds thru this gun and never had a jam, or failure of any kind. It is remarkably accurate out to 15 yards, maybe longer, but I have not tried farther than 15 yards.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 625 JM Revolver Competition Rig
location: South Minneapollis, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
All Right Folks.......

Here it is.... The ULTIMATE Competition Revolver.

S&W 625 JM 4" model revolver, N Frame, chambered in .45 ACP with competition upgrade and aftermarket grips.

This isn't your ordinary JM model S&W. This has every upgrade in the book sans optics, and really.... Who would put optics on a competition revovler......

In addition to this being one of the most sought after compeitions rigs on the market, this revolver has had a complete trigger job, the cylinder has been chamfered for ease of reloading, the hammer has been bobbed to reduce lockup time and it has an upgraded high performance spring kit. It also features the gold dot front sight.

The result? A competition revolver (double action only), chambered in .45 ACP that has a silky smooth 5lb trigger pull.... yes, a 5lb double action pull... and is easier to reload than most autos out there. The grip is made much more stable as a result of the aftermarket Hogue grip with the wooden pinky kick. This truly is one of the finest shooting revolvers I have ever seen.

The drawback? You will need to use rounds loaded with Federal 150 primers for consistent ignition. This can easily be brought back to setting off factory ammo, but you will sarifice the unbelievable trigger pull that I believe One person who shot it called "Awesome Sauce".  I do have the factory springs (included), and a new hammer is inexpensive if one were to want to bring it back to the original setup.

Anyone who has shot this will want it. Those that can't afford it will tell you I'm insane for selling it. Which begs the question.... Why? WHY IN GOD'S NAME WOULD I SELL THIS GEM???

Easy. I have two.  I prefer the 5" model, and don't see the need to have both of them when I'm trying to make room in the safe.

What is included with this? The revolver, the kick ass custom competition upgrade,a brick of Federal 150 primers (1,000 count to get you started) a CR Speed belt (adjustable up to 42") and a fabulous kydex competition holster. I can't remember the make, but I bought it New 2 years ago for around $70. It is fully adjustable for retention and cant, and is in perfect condition. I also have a bundle of moon clips for this, since they are necessary.

Full disclosure..... there is minor holster wear on this gun, and it has over a thousand rounds through it. The rounds have all been lead round nose, and loaded right at the Major power floor, so no wear from that. Anyone who knows S&W revolvers will tell you that a few thousand rounds isn't even enough to break this thing in.  

THIS IS NOT A SELF DEFENSE GUN. Please don't buy this with the intent of wearing it as a personal potection gun. It is meant for competition and range work, and should only be used on the range. It has been exceptionally reliable for me when used properly, but you do not want to trust your life to this thing.

Now on the the money.... Will not ship, will not travel too far, FTF only, PTP or PTC only, valid DL required. NO exceptions.

I'm asking $1000 for the package, which really is a steal. I would consider trades, but cash is king. Trades considered.... Old military rifles +cash, (rare variant Mosins, stock Enfields, Field grade Garand, etc.) Kahr CW45 + cash, Deer rig in .243 + cash and ???? I don't know.... run it by me!  Worst I can say is no.

No lowball offers, $1k is fair for the package as it sits. 

Since I can't seem to get images to link here, and Armslist won't let me post a link to my Flickr account or post images over 4mb total, email me for a batch of High resolution, high quality pictures of this revolver.
